---
description: TypeScript interface & enum naming in apps/api
globs: apps/api/**/*.ts
alwaysApply: false
---

# Interface modules (`apps/api`)

- Put interface-only modules in files named **`kebab-case.interface.ts`** (e.g. `notification.interface.ts`, `notification-document.interface.ts`).
- **Do not** use `INotification.ts`, `inotification.ts`, or other `I`-prefixed filenames for the file itself; the exported symbol may still be `INotification` if desired.
- One primary interface (or a small, closely related set) per file is fine; split when files grow or domains diverge.
- Import these without a `.js` extension to match existing `apps/api` convention.

# Enums (`apps/api`)

- Name exported enums with an **`Enum` suffix**, not `Type` (e.g. **`ActorEnum`**, **`NotificationEnum`** — not `ActorType` / `NotificationType`).
- Keep enum definitions in **`enums/models/`** (or a similar clear folder) with one concern per file when practical (e.g. `actor.ts`, `notification.ts`).
